The paper deals with super-resolution of texture maps for 3D objects, which is a problem in computer graphics and computer vision. The paper proposes a neural network architecture that combines multi-view super-resolution and single-view super-resolution. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Graphics (cs.GR) categories. The paper also mentions the use of a learned prior for high-resolution image structure, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents experimental results that involve processing images, which suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category.
